com.axonivy.jmx

Annotation Type MSizeAttribute


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={FIELD,METHOD})
 @Inherited
public @interface MSizeAttribute
    Use this annotation to manage the size of an object as attribute on a MBean. The following object types are supported:
    • Collection -> Attribute value: Collection.size()
    • Map -> Attribute value: Map.size()
    • String -> Attribute value: String.length()
    Example: 
      @MBean
 class MyBean
 {
    @MSizeAttribute
   private List strings;
 }
    This will provide an attribute with the name strings. The value is the number of Strings in the List.
    Since:
    28.06.2013
    Author:
    rwei
